DESCRIPTION:Biological Mechanisms of PTSD: Integrating Genomic\, Epigenomi
 c\, and Immune Perspectives\n\nThe Broad Trauma Initiative (BTI) invites y
 ou to join us for the June 25th Brain Biology Program Meeting and Broad Tr
 auma Initiative Special Seminar from 2:00-3:30PM at the Broad Institute of
  MIT and Harvard\, hosted by Dr. Karestan Koenen and featuring PTSD geneti
 cs researchers from across the country.\n\nSpeakers: \n\nCaroline Nieverge
 lt\, PhD\, professor of psychiatry at UC San Diego: “Fulfilling the Prom
 ise of GWAS: Large-Scale Genomic Discovery in PTSD”\n\nAlicia Smith\, Ph
 D\, professor and vice chair of research in the Department of Gynecology a
 nd Obstetrics at Emory University School of Medicine: “Trauma\, Immunity
 \, and the Epigenome: Biological Mechanisms Underlying PTSD”\n\nMonica U
 ddin\, PhD\, professor of Global\, Environmental\, and Genomic Health Scie
 nces at the University of South Florida: "Biologic mechanisms linking geno
 cide exposure to PTSD in Rwanda”\n\nHosted by Karestan Koenen\, PhD\n\nP
 lease complete this brief RSVP form if you plan to attend the meeting.\n\n
 Event URL: https://events.broadinstitute.org/event/brain-biology-program-m
 eeting-and-broad-trauma-initiative-special-seminar\n\nSource: broad_instit
 ute
LOCATION:Stanley Building (75A)\, Yellowstone
URL:https://events.broadinstitute.org/event/brain-biology-program-meeting-
 and-broad-trauma-initiative-special-seminar
